1. In any java file, at most 1 package statement should be there.
eg.
package p1;
package p2;  -------> (this will give compile time error)
public class Test {}

2. In any java program, the first not commented statement should be package statement.
eg.
import java.util.*;
package p1;  ---------> (this will give compile time error)
public class Test {}


ORDER OF STATEMENTS:
PACKAGE STATEMENT (at most 1)        |
IMPORT STATEMENTS (any number)       |     *order is important
CLASS/INTERFACE/ENUM (any number)    |
                                     V